  <title>Polynomial Functions</title>

<commentary audience="instructor"><title>Overview</title>
<p>In this Lesson we consider polynomials, and specifically cubes of binomials and factoring the sum or difference of cubes. We also look at some simple poynomial models.</p></commentary> 

<activity><title>Polynomials</title>

            <commentary audience="instructor"><title>Note</title>
            <p>You may need to review the vocabulary of polynomials: degree, coefficient, descending powers, monomial, binomial, and trinomial.</p></commentary>

<task><p>Write the definition of a polynomial function.</p></task>  
 
 <task><p>Give an example of a trinomial of degree four whose lead coefficient is <m>~-5</m>.</p></task>
  
<task><p>Multiply  <m>~(3x-2)(4x^2+x-2)</m></p></task>

<task><p>Multiply  <m>~(2a^2-3a+1)(3a^2+2a-1)</m></p></task>

          <commentary audience="instructor"><title>Note</title>
          <p>Students can usually multiply polynomials without difficulty, but you will have to show them how to find a specific term of the product. This is a good exercise for analyzing what could be just a rote manipulation.</p></commentary>

